additional_definition: Make keen or more acute. Sharpen by rubbing, as on a whetstone

Primary Definition: a fanciful impulse, or whimsical idea

synonyms: Notion. whim. whimsy. whimsey. Caprice. impulse. whim

Primary Definition: given to whimsy or fanciful notions
additional_definition: Determined by chance or impulse or whim rather than by necessity or reason
sample sentences: A capricious refusal. Authoritarian rulers are frequently capricious. The victim of whimsical persecutions

Primary Definition: to utter a complaining cry or sound
additional_definition: Make a high-pitched, screeching noise. Talk in a tearful manner. Complain whiningly. Move with a whining sound
sample sentences: The bullets were whining past us. The door creaked when I opened it slowly. My car engine makes a whining noise

Primary Definition: entirely

Primary Definition: sweetly or innocently charming
additional_definition: Charming in a childlike or naive way

Primary Definition: suggestive or characteristic of winter, cold, stormy

Primary Definition: thin, muscular and flexible

Primary Definition: like a slender, flexible strand or bundle

Primary Definition: amusingly clever in perception and expression

Wrench a window off its hinges. Wrench oneself free from somebody's grip. A deep sigh was wrenched from his chest

additional_definition: A fear of foreigners or strangers
